My meme

My meme is the apathetic Winnie vs fancy Winnie Winnie the Pooh Meme which have always made me laugh, as I think Fancy Winnie looks ridiculous. My meme is different because I made it applicable to this course - I often get told I sound way cooler when I people Im doing a data science paper rather than a stats paper, so this meme is a funny way to represent that. 

##importing the magic library to use magick functions for my code
library(magick)



##Sourcing and naming the two winnie images.
##couch winnie sits on the couch, whereas tuxedo winnie sits on the couch looking much fancier.
couch_winnie <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/001/474/942/012.gif") %>%
  image_scale(558)

tuxedo_winnie <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/001/474/943/b12.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(558)



##Creating the two textboxes (containing the text parts of the meme) to go alongside the winnie images.
stats_textbox <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                                   height = 500, 
                                   color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I'm doing a\nstats paper.",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 70,
                 font = "Arial",
                 gravity = "center")

data_science_textbox <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                                      height = 500, 
                                      color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I'm studying\ndata science.",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 70,
                 font = "Arial",
                 gravity = "center")


##appending the winnie images to their corresponding textboxes, done in two halves to stack on top of each other.
top_half <- c(couch_winnie, stats_textbox) %>%
  image_append()

bottom_half <- c(tuxedo_winnie, data_science_textbox) %>%
  image_append()



##appending the two halves to create then final meme, and assigning a label to it 
meme <- c(top_half, bottom_half) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

##saving the meme as the image file "my_meme.png"
meme %>% image_write("my_meme.png")
body {
  font-family: Times;
  color: #E3056C;
}

My animated gif

My gif is a beating heart with my UPI inside to make it a bit more personal. I used a pink heart image to create 20 frames at different sizes with my UPI inside,then animated them together. My UPI grows at a slightly different rate to add a bit more of a 3D effect to my beating heart. 

##importing the magic library to use magick functions for my code
library(magick)

##frames from 1-20 of slightly different sizes for 'smooth' heartbeat.
##the text, my UPI, changes size at a slightly different ratio doe 'heartbeat' look more 3D
frame1 <- image_read("http://clipart-library.com/images/gceoe55qi.gif") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "VRYA365",
                 font = "Times",
                 size = 40, 
                 gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(200) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")
